What you need to know:

The two-thirds gender rule is just one of the many troubles facing women as Kenya prepares for another election in August.At the centre of it is how political parties—and politicians in particular—treat women, with this bad treatment starting right at the nominations, the all-important precursor of the General Election.A study by the by IDEA says most parties will hand women hopefuls a ticket in areas where the outfits are unpopular.